Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:06.61,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,There is no value in a country \Nthat has lost all its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.94,0:00:09.74,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,When a nation's collapse \Nis only a matter of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.74,0:00:12.49,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,the only question is how \Nto deal the final blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.19,0:00:15.62,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,I have a request to make of you, Prince Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.15,0:00:21.83,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Won't you first form a \Nmodest alliance with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.22,0:00:25.82,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,In order to avoid a future in \Nwhich Coyolles is destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.82,0:00:28.71,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I've formed an alliance with Prince Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.36,0:00:30.22,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.43,0:00:35.72,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,If it were Arnold Hein, then I have the \Nfeeling that he'd use it quite effectively...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.28,0:00:39.10,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,this compound I've created,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.76,0:00:42.31,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,which I call black powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.60,0:00:45.60,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Professor Michel's aim is to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.60,0:00:49.30,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,how large an effect black \Npowder will have on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.77,0:00:51.85,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,To achieve that end, the professor
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.85,0:00:55.40,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,will surely point out black \Npowder's power to Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.07,0:01:00.12,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I must find a way to stop the professor's \Nexperiment, no matter what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.53,0:03:04.54,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,These are leto fireflies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.54,0:03:06.31,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,They're so beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.40,0:03:36.30,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,G-Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.40,0:03:38.14,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.68,0:03:47.82,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.26,0:03:49.47,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,They're fireflies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.05,0:03:50.89,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Fireflies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.08,0:03:58.21,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,If you wish for them to be \Nexterminated, I'll give the order.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.21,0:03:59.71,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.06,0:04:02.88,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,If they're fireflies, then \Nthey're bugs, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.88,0:04:06.35,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, they are bugs, but you mustn't \Nthoughtlessly exterminate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.22,0:04:12.43,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,All animals, humans included, are \Npart of one large cycle, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.94,0:04:17.11,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.32,0:04:22.82,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,You see? They're so beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.16,0:04:29.33,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.84,0:04:36.02,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,What a strange feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.02,0:04:41.08,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,All of the things I'm worried about \Nstem from His Highness, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.20,0:04:50.47,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Somehow they all seem to be flying \Ntoward Your Highness, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.47,0:04:52.38,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Then you should just come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.94,0:04:56.02,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I suppose you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.32,0:04:57.83,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,This much would probably be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:01.32,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Hey. You wouldn't—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.83,0:05:37.02,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.81,0:05:39.32,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.56,0:05:44.66,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,If I startled you, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.25,0:05:46.84,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,But I, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.85,0:05:51.07,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,You do know, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.07,0:05:55.35,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I can jump a distance like \Nthat with no problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.35,0:06:02.84,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Yes. After all, you can jump down \Nto the ground from a palace balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.32,0:06:04.92,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, why...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.37,0:06:13.35,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Even though I know, I moved \Nreflexively. I couldn't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.68,0:06:37.57,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.58,0:06:43.38,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You do realize that you could have gone out \Ninto the hallway and come through the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.91,0:06:46.14,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Through the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.42,0:06:47.50,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Through the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.16,0:06:50.13,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.61,0:06:55.56,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,The way you cut across via the shortest \Nroute is just like that other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:06:57.85,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Whatever could you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.07,0:07:03.74,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,By the way, why do you have your sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.52,0:07:09.35,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I mistook the light of the \Nfireflies for torches.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:13.57,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Now that he mentions it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.57,0:07:16.38,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,their light does resemble the \Ntorches you see on a battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.01,0:07:24.82,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Memories of the war are vividly, \Ndeeply embedded within him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.51,0:07:44.86,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,They truly are...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.32,0:07:47.09,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,such beautiful eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.43,0:07:54.96,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,These eyes are the same color as my father's.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.55,0:07:58.86,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,They serve as proof that I carry the \Nsame blood as my father, the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:04.44,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,When I was a child, I very much \Nwanted to gouge both of my eyes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.17,0:08:06.19,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.19,0:08:12.30,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,They aren't something you \Nshould gaze at in that manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.17,0:08:19.48,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,There is a deep hostility between Prince \NArnold and his father which seems boundless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.45,0:08:27.58,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,The day you first came to this palace, you \Nsaid you had an admiration for this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.72,0:08:33.90,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I am unable to feel admiration \Nin the same way that you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.35,0:08:36.72,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,The light of fireflies looks \Nlike the fires of war...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.72,0:08:39.24,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,and looking down from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.24,0:08:41.89,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,the view of the capital is infuriating to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.89,0:08:45.32,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Perhaps it's because of these eyes \NI've inherited from my father,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.32,0:08:46.93,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,or perhaps it's because of my nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.92,0:08:51.50,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Either way, it doesn't change the \Nfact that it's repulsive to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.36,0:09:01.42,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Lights seen from far away might look like \Nwartime fires or like firefly lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.42,0:09:04.98,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The values inherent to such a perception \Naren't inherited from one's parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.98,0:09:08.34,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,they are gained through all the \Nthings a person has experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:12.23,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,In which case, you just need to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:16.75,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Learn about the beauty of this nation and \Nthe magnificent things that live in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:20.24,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,In the future yet to come, you \Ncan do that as much as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.34,0:09:23.33,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I have no need of such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.78,0:09:27.04,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,As long as there are things I can use \Nto achieve my aims, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.04,0:09:28.01,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.55,0:09:32.67,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I've even killed people I \Nheld dear with my own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.17,0:09:36.88,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Even you. If you ever become an \Nimpediment, I'll discard you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.92,0:09:42.07,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,On the matter of Coyolles, I don't \Nknow what you might be thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.13,0:09:46.41,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,but don't make me have to get rid of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.08,0:09:52.20,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I can't promise you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.20,0:09:57.44,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Should I become your wife, I will \Nstill move to achieve my own aims.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.44,0:10:00.22,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even if that means you cast me aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.23,0:10:04.21,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.29,0:10:08.54,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,when that happens, I'll \Nsimply return here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.54,0:10:09.38,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:14.21,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even if you cast me aside and \Ndeclare our engagement broken,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.21,0:10:18.43,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'll interview to become a maid \Nand return to this palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.53,0:10:22.00,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,If that doesn't work, I'll dress \Nas a man and become a knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.00,0:10:24.43,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,And if that doesn't work, \NI'll come as an herbalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.96,0:10:28.27,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'll acquire whatever skills seem like \Nthey'll let me slip back into the palace,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.27,0:10:30.44,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,and I'll come to see you again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.28,0:10:33.27,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,So please, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.27,0:10:37.44,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I won't stand by and allow you \Nto get rid of me, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.41,0:10:49.83,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,To me, these eyes are \Nyour eyes, Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.51,0:10:53.48,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even if you, yourself, detest them,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.48,0:10:55.76,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I want to tell you this \Nover and over again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.97,0:11:02.55,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I think your eyes are the most \Nbeautiful in all the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:13.21,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's late. Go and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.02,0:11:17.35,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.10,0:11:18.83,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.16,0:11:32.42,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,When I was a child, I very much \Nwanted to gouge both of my eyes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.85,0:12:13.58,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Please look these over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.08,0:12:19.05,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Coyolles' techniques truly are splendid!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.05,0:12:20.64,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.64,0:12:24.81,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,And the finely powdered metals you \Nrequested are right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.49,0:12:27.94,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,To be honest, I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.94,0:12:32.35,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even the trading company I patronize \Nhas difficulty obtaining all of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.67,0:12:35.30,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,We've formed an alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.30,0:12:37.36,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Naturally, I should \Ndo everything in my power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.76,0:12:39.34,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.90,0:12:41.57,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,You feel that way because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.57,0:12:45.40,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,you've built honest relationships \Nwith so many traders, Prince Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.27,0:12:50.77,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I've managed to obtain an appointment to \Nspeak with Prince Arnold one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.90,0:12:55.50,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,But will this really be \Nenough to convince him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.32,0:12:57.63,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.63,0:13:01.34,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,But I'm confident it will be \Nenough to entice him to listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.85,0:13:04.12,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,How can you say that with such certainty?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.12,0:13:05.84,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,It is, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.56,0:13:10.56,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,because I am Prince Arnold's future wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.11,0:14:03.14,Default,Theodore's vassal 1,0,0,0,,Wh-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.88,0:14:04.91,Default,Theodore's vassal 1,0,0,0,,What's going...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.35,0:14:17.87,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Thank you for granting me your time today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.87,0:14:19.90,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I will say this in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.90,0:14:22.88,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I have no intention of having \Nthe same conversation again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.32,0:14:27.57,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I still feel that there is no value \Nin an alliance with Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.47,0:14:30.20,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I understand your position.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.20,0:14:31.51,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.51,0:14:35.27,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I assume you've brought a \Nsomewhat worthwhile proposal?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.27,0:14:37.02,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Of course, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.03,0:14:39.98,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I can't allow myself to be daunted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.98,0:14:42.51,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,This is a negotiation. It's a battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:47.16,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You sit, too. Let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.16,0:14:48.72,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Before that, Your Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.59,0:14:53.66,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,can you tell exactly how I differ \Nfrom my usual self today?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:14:59.79,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Earrings. Bracelet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.30,0:15:01.67,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Necklaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:03.80,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,None of them are familiar to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.80,0:15:06.42,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You've never worn them \Nwith me before, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.61,0:15:09.09,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's just as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.44,0:15:13.54,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,All of these pieces are \Njewelry made in Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.54,0:15:17.26,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,In addition to producing metals and gems,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.26,0:15:20.71,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,my kingdom is cut off by \Nsnow for over half the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.24,0:15:23.79,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Given the aforementioned conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.79,0:15:27.12,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,we have advanced the craft of jewelry \Nmaking, which can be done indoors,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.12,0:15:29.86,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,and we have cultivated \Nmany brilliant artisans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.44,0:15:33.14,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Even those items, which other countries \Nhave difficulty producing,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.14,0:15:37.49,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,can be completed quickly\Nand exquisitely by our artisans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.89,0:15:41.36,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,We in Coyolles stand proudly before the \Nentire world and say that this is our treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.59,0:15:55.44,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I will make a declaration here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.57,0:16:16.12,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,You recognize this item, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.12,0:16:17.74,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Well, it does belong to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.23,0:16:19.52,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,What of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.68,0:16:21.16,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,This is—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.16,0:16:22.16,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.72,0:16:26.92,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,It can't be. I never imagined \Nthat you would notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.12,0:16:32.17,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,This isn't the piece that \NYour Highness lent to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.17,0:16:34.30,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,It is a reproduction of that watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.68,0:16:38.44,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold, your watch is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.76,0:16:44.65,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,We borrowed jewelers' equipment\Nand were able to cast all of the parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.12,0:16:48.56,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The one who created this reproduction \Nwas a jeweler from Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.52,0:16:54.72,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Intricate metalworking was used \Nto create the gears and screws.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.72,0:16:58.23,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,As my kingdom's artisan has accurately \Nreproduced the piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.23,0:17:00.47,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,we are now able to repair it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.47,0:17:05.08,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold, you are already aware of the \Nmagnificence of this ware called a watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.76,0:17:08.02,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,These watches are rare in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.02,0:17:10.62,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,but have you never wished you could \Npossess them in large numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.35,0:17:17.15,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Or perhaps you've imagined turning the \Nskills used to produce them to other uses?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.72,0:17:22.60,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Research into technologies which might use \Ngears and clockwork has already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.89,0:17:25.12,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Carriages that can move \Neven without horses...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.12,0:17:27.18,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Ships that can sail even without wind...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.76,0:17:31.29,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,In the not-so-distant future, \Npeople may dream of such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.77,0:17:33.36,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,However, when that time comes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:37.48,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,the only country with the skills to make \Nthose dreams a reality will be Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.90,0:17:40.87,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,And, Prince Arnold...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.23,0:17:43.62,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm certain that you will want them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.05,0:17:47.14,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,You will want to bring their \Ntechnical prowess to Galkhein!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.97,0:17:53.21,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Is that all?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.09,0:17:57.33,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Kyle Morgan Cleverly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.92,0:18:00.25,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,What are you trying to do here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.40,0:18:06.30,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I acknowledge that the skills your \Ncountry possesses are exceptional.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.86,0:18:09.66,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It is something which my nation lacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.61,0:18:16.11,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Which is why, all the more, I \Nfind your naïvety revolting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.29,0:18:21.43,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,There is no need to form an alliance \Nto obtain another country's technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.43,0:18:24.78,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Because everything can be taken \Nthrough military force, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.50,0:18:28.55,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Did you come here without a single thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.55,0:18:30.75,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Did you simply do as my future wife said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.37,0:18:33.44,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,and come here as ornamental royalty?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.94,0:18:37.77,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe, you're no better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.77,0:18:40.39,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Say that I obtained this technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.82,0:18:43.75,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Did you never imagine \Nwhat I might use it for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.83,0:18:48.99,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Using metalworking technologies \Nas a piece in negotiations...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.92,0:18:52.51,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,When this was suggested to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.51,0:18:55.15,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I thought you might not be pleased by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.53,0:18:58.78,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,However, Lady Rishe believed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.33,0:19:02.86,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,"The power to make the future \Na more wonderful place..."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.86,0:19:05.73,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,"It isn't possible that Prince \NArnold won't want that," she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.38,0:19:11.79,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I, too, came to this country because \Nof my belief in you, Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.27,0:19:14.57,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,You are an outstanding ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.57,0:19:18.68,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,And during the war, you showed even \Nenemy nations a form of respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.26,0:19:22.99,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,The reality is that you're kind enough to \Nbe here, like this, in discussions with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.99,0:19:25.31,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,That is a naïve way of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.34,0:19:32.31,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,My foolishness lies in thinking to \Nrely on you, to have you protect us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.31,0:19:36.69,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,But my decision, the thought that I \Nwanted to form an alliance with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.69,0:19:38.69,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I don't believe that that was a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:43.20,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,The intellectual power \Nof Coyolles' scholars...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.77,0:19:45.95,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,and our metalworking technologies...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.26,0:19:49.91,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,If we continue to research these \Ntwo things together with your country,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.91,0:19:54.21,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,then this future that Lady Rishe \Nspeaks of won't be simply a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.65,0:19:58.12,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,If it will gain your trust,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.82,0:20:00.98,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I will spare nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.59,0:20:11.98,Default,Oliver,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry to interrupt \Nyour conversation, Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.44,0:20:15.20,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I hope you are doing well, Prince Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.20,0:20:18.94,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I offer my deepest apologies for my \Nrudeness in disturbing your conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.94,0:20:22.62,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Brother, I am very sorry to interrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:26.99,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,An emergency?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:31.50,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry. I will excuse \Nmyself here for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.50,0:20:32.98,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,L-Lady Rishe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.98,0:20:34.91,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm really very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.91,0:20:36.06,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,If you'll excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.59,0:20:42.36,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Everyone I had shadowing the \Ntarget was given the slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.98,0:20:46.66,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,We were last certain of his \Nwhereabouts three hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.66,0:20:48.92,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,He was in a back street in Section 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.92,0:20:50.89,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What was the situation when \Nthey lost sight of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.89,0:20:53.21,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Apparently, there was \Nsome sort of sweet smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.21,0:20:56.24,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,When they woke, the target's \Nwhereabouts were unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.85,0:21:00.61,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Which means that the surveillance \Nof Michel Hévin has failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.16,0:21:06.34,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Well, that seemed hurried.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.34,0:21:10.97,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I offer my apologies as well for my future \Nwife and younger brother's rudeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.97,0:21:12.48,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Not at all. If we could continue—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.48,0:21:13.42,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Oliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.04,0:21:24.35,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.88,0:21:26.64,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,What is all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.38,0:21:34.45,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Theodore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.45,0:21:35.79,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.79,0:21:39.90,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Just as you thought, that man \Nwas carrying a large bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.57,0:21:43.43,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I've already mobilized \Neveryone in from the slums.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.43,0:21:45.41,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,They're looking into the contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.41,0:21:46.65,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.44,0:21:50.41,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,But there is one thing that's bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.21,0:21:53.16,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.16,0:21:53.96,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.56,0:21:57.19,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,I may be the second prince,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.19,0:21:59.58,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,but that isn't enough to allow \Nme to barge into a meeting of his.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.12,0:22:03.08,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,And he didn't seem at all surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.59,0:22:06.59,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.21,0:22:10.06,Default,Theodore,0,0,0,,We know where that man is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.89,0:22:24.07,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.62,0:22:30.31,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Hey there, Rishe.
